milestones.description: Alei Nao and Norman Vanua's 37-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 28 between Alei Nao and Chad Soper
Norman Vanua has become the top wicket-taker for PNG in ODIs with 20 wickets, going past Chad Soper's 19
Assad Vala has broken the record for most catches (8) in ODIs for PNG, going past Vani Morea's 7
Vani Morea has scored 3 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for PNG breaking Mahuru Dai's record
Lega Siaka has scored 1 hundreds in ODIs, the most for PNG breaking Tony Ura's record
Mahuru Dai has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (17) for PNG, going past Assad Vala

stories.title: Holder and Brathwaite ward off PNG threat
stories.subTitle: Papua New Guinea v West Indies, World Cup Qualifier, Harare
stories.seoTitle: Jason Holder and Carlos Brathwaite ward off Papua New Guinea threat
stories.summary: For a few moments, West Indies looked in danger of losing to Papua New Guinea, chasing a target of 201. But their captain Jason Holder took charge to lead the team across the line

recentReportStory.subTitle: Papua New Guinea v West Indies, World Cup Qualifier, Harare
recentReportStory.seoTitle: Jason Holder and Carlos Brathwaite ward off Papua New Guinea threat
recentReportStory.summary: For a few moments, West Indies looked in danger of losing to Papua New Guinea, chasing a target of 201. But their captain Jason Holder took charge to lead the team across the line
